### ============================================================
### Push notifications — endpoint smoke tests
### ------------------------------------------------------------
### These hit the same endpoints the mobile Push screen calls. Use
### them to confirm the backend wiring WITHOUT a device:
###   1. Register a (real or placeholder) Expo push token.
###   2. Send the test notification.
###   3. Read the in-app `notifications` row back.
###
### For REAL device delivery, register the token from the mobile
### Push screen (it calls POST /device-tokens). The token must match
### `^(ExponentPushToken|ExpoPushToken)\[.+\]$`.
###
### Run in the "local" (or "device") environment from
### rest-client.env.json. The login block below captures
### @accessToken / @refreshToken for every request that follows.
### ============================================================
### ============================================================
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### capture tokens
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}
@refreshToken = {{login.response.body.data.refreshToken}}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### Register a device token for the current user
### Use the real Expo token from the mobile Push screen, or a
### placeholder Expo-format token for backend-only smoke testing.
### Expect 201 { data:{ id, platform } }
### ------------------------------------------------------------
# @name registerToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/notifications/device-tokens
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pushToken": "ExponentPushToken[xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx]",
  "platform": "android"
}

###

### Register with a malformed token (expect 400 VALIDATION_ERROR)
POST {{baseUrl}}/notifications/device-tokens
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pushToken": "not-a-real-token",
  "platform": "android"
}

###

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### Send a test push to the current user's registered device(s)
### Expect 200 { data:{ sent:true, deduped:false } }
### On a real device the notification arrives via Expo → FCM/APNs.
### ------------------------------------------------------------
# @name sendTest
POST {{baseUrl}}/notifications/test
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### Unregister the device token
### Expect 200 { data:{ success:true } }
### ------------------------------------------------------------
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/notifications/device-tokens
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pushToken": "ExponentPushToken[xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx]"
}

###
